  "texts": [
    "Thus, addressing normality drift is crucial for maintaining the effectiveness and reliability of anomaly detection systems.R14 -Enhance Normality Drift Detection.",
    "Han et al. [78] introduced OWAD as a solution to combat the challenge of normality drift encountered in deep learning-based anomaly detection for security applications.",
    "OWAD serves as a framework designed to detect, explain, and adapt to normality shifts at the distribution level, departing from sample-level explanations like CADE [258] which fail to comprehensively address the holistic shift in distribution, thereby limiting their applicability in understanding the overall normality drift.",
    "This development paves the way for numerous future research opportunities in anomaly detection.",
    "Particularly, there exists potential for exploring innovative adaptation strategies within OWAD aimed at enhancing its efficacy in adapting to evolving data distributions."
  ],
